{"tid":567140,"cid":6,"subCid":0,"title":"[英格蘭新希望？] 牙買加Leon Bailly 有望入選英格蘭國家隊","createTime":"2018-02-20T14:54:42.000Z","updateTime":"2018-02-20T16:32:49.000Z","uid":155079,"like":2,"dislike":0,"uniUserReply":5,"replies":[{"pid":"a898c3cf6710dad5fd5be2ec9b2134a8888244ed","tid":567140,"uid":155079,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2018-02-20T14:54:42.000Z","msg":"Bayer Leverkusen sensation Leon Bailey could be in line for a shock England call-up ahead of the World Cup in Russia. <br />\n<br />\nSources close to the player have reportedly confirmed the player has British ancestry, with The Mirror stating that two of the 20-year-old's grandparents possess British passports.<br />\n<br />\nIt is understood that England's recruitment team have been keeping tabs on the winger, who also qualifies to represent his country of birth Jamaica, as well as Malta.<br />\n<br />\nBailey has already represented Jamaica at Under-23 level, but he has yet to pledge his allegiance, and has always been open about his desire to play for a bigger nation.<br />\n<br />\nSpeaking to Bild previously, the former Genk forward said: 'Which country I play for is still open. <br />\n<br />\n'It's been like that for years, but my opinion hasn&rsquo;t changed and people have to accept that.'<br />\n<br />\nBailey has been a revelation in the Bundesliga this term, scoring nine times in 23 appearances as Leverkusen chase a Champions League spot. <br />\n<br />\nHe was in action at the weekend, netting the first goal as Heiko Herrlich's side beat Hamburg 2-1 as they stayed third, behind Borussia Dortmund and runaway leaders Bayern Munich. <br />\n<br />\nUsed predominantly down the flank, Manchester United are one of several top clubs around Europe to have been linked with him over the past 12 months.<br />\n<br />\nSource: Dailymail"},{"pid":"813d8c3df460994df9fd9c6481a3084e6d8b66b2","tid":567140,"uid":54025,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":1,"replyTime":"2018-02-20T14:56: